        <body>       
                 
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>DR. J. SOLIS&#45;COHEN&#44;<lb/>
                OFFICE HOURS&#58; 9&#45;1.<lb/></p>
            <p>1431 Walnut Street&#44;<lb/>
                Philadelphia&#44; Sep 6 1887<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear teacher&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>One word is<lb/> worth a dozen letters.<lb/>  I hope to see you and<lb/> explain.  You misunder&#45;<lb/>stand my design&#59; which<lb/> is to prevent any such<lb/> contingency as you refer to&#44;<lb/> by having something done<lb/> by you&#44; under your own<lb/> direction and control &#40;and perfectly satisfactory to you&#41; which<lb/> shall be final.  As we<lb/> cannot bring the others<lb/> to us on a ritual<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>complete&#45;&#45;What I<lb/> desired was to have<lb/> something all could<lb/> agree on&#44; and an<lb/> agreement to disagree<lb/> about the rest&#45;&#45;Mendes<lb/> experiment shows nothing<lb/> is to be hoped for from<lb/> abroad.  I am decidedly<lb/> opposed to having any<lb/> <hi rend="underline">congregation</hi> take the <sic>inia&#45;<lb/>tive</sic>&#45;&#45;because every fool<lb/> would want his own<lb/> ideas.  Therefore as<lb/> you have taught that<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>2&#41;<lb/></p>
            <p>something should be<lb/> done&#44; I want you to<lb/> take the lead in doing<lb/> it.  I consider the Synod<lb/> only a formal matter<lb/> to give a colorable au&#45;<lb/>thority.  For my own part<lb/> I am frank to say that<lb/> I consider your authority<lb/> all&#45;sufficient&#45;&#45;as was<lb/> Hillel&#39;s when the time de&#45;<lb/>manded prompt and decisive<lb/> action.  However I can<lb/> explain better when we have<lb/> a talk.  Affectionately<lb/> J. S. C.<lb/> over<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>My proposition is<lb/> simply this&#45;&#45;<lb/> Shall you construct<lb/> a proper liturgy once<lb/> and for all&#45;&#45;which<lb/> shall be the means of<lb/> stopping fools from talking<lb/> and of improving the ser&#45;<lb/>vices&#45;&#45;<lb/> or shall the present mis&#45;<lb/>erable plan of every arro&#45;<lb/>gant and ignorant Parnass<lb/> or Trustee&#44; and subservient<lb/> &#34;Rabbi&#34; mutilating <hi rend="underline">ad libitum</hi><lb/> be allowed to continue&#63;&#45;&#45;<lb/> In restricting our confab to<lb/> the <hi rend="underline">liturgy</hi> we avoid all questions<lb/> of pews&#44; organs &#38;c&#44; and therefore<lb/> disagreement or change.<lb/></p>
            </body>
